title: Asher Keddie and her husband look flustered at Sydney Airport
text:
Holidays can be a stressful experience for most families.

And Asher Keddie and her husband Vincent Fantauzzo are certainly no exception, after they were pictured looking rather flustered at Sydney Airport last month.

In photos taken on September 26, the couple appeared a little stressed out after landing with their sons Valentino, four, and Luca, nine.

Holidays can be stressful! Asher Keddie and her husband Vincent Fantauzzo were pictured looking rather flustered at Sydney Airport last month

At one stage, the 45-year-old Offspring star gestured with her hands while seemingly making a point to Vincent.

The couple, who married in 2014, then walked towards the car park alongside their children, after what appeared to have been a long day.

Fortunately, the stress of traveling as a family seemed to fade away once they located their vehicle.

Shady lady: For her flight home, Asher wore a pair of large sunglasses and styled her blonde hair in a scruffy updo

For her flight home, Asher wore a pair of large sunglasses and styled her blonde hair in a scruffy updo.

She went makeup free for the trip, and dressed casually in comfortable trousers, a leather jacket and white sneakers.

It comes after Asher delighted fans last month with an unexpected announcement.

Keeping it simple: Asher went makeup free for the trip, and dressed casually in comfortable trousers, a leather jacket and white sneakers

Taking to Instagram, she revealed that all seven seasons of Australian TV show Offspring are now available to stream on Netflix.

'So thrilled that Offspring is reaching far and wide,' she told her 53,000 followers.

Asher, who is now a Myer ambassador, played Dr Nina Proudman on the Channel 10 drama from 2010 to 2017.

Phew! The apparent stress of traveling as a family seemed to fade away once they located their vehicle in the airport car park
